# Two subdomains, per tech.md 3 and 17.5: the mini app on one, only Marzban's /sub/* on the other.
#
# READ BEFORE HARDENING THIS FILE. Two headers are missing on purpose:
#
#   X-Frame-Options — any value breaks the mini app. Telegram Web and Desktop run it inside an
#   iframe, so DENY/SAMEORIGIN blank the app for those clients. tech.md 9 says: do not set it at all.
#
#   Content-Security-Policy — hooks.server.ts already sends `frame-ancestors https://web.telegram.org
#   https://*.telegram.org`. Setting a CSP here overwrites that response header and locks Telegram
#   out of the frame, which is the same outage by another route. The app owns this header.
#
# Both look like obvious wins from a proxy config and are both outages. Leave them alone.
#
# HSTS is the exception and belongs HERE rather than in the app: caddy terminates TLS, so it is the
# only party that knows the connection was HTTPS at all. The app sits behind it on plain HTTP.

{
	# ACME notifications and expiry warnings. Replace before launch.
	email admin@example.com
}

# A17 — one year, subdomains included. Both hosts are HTTPS-only and caddy already redirects :80,
# but the redirect is one plaintext round trip a network can intercept; HSTS removes it after the
# first visit.
#
# `preload` is deliberately NOT set: it is a one-way door, submitted out of band, and it would bind
# every future subdomain of this apex to HTTPS forever. Add it once the domains are settled.
(hsts) {
	header Strict-Transport-Security "max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains"
}

app.example.com {
	import hsts
	encode zstd gzip

	# The only way into the app: it never publishes 3000 to the host.
	reverse_proxy app:3000

	log
}

sub.example.com {
	import hsts
	encode zstd gzip

	# Clients need their subscription link and nothing else. The panel, /api and /dashboard stay on
	# the docker network, reachable only through an SSH tunnel (tech.md 3, tech.md 9). Marzban
	# builds these URLs from XRAY_SUBSCRIPTION_URL_PREFIX, so the path stays /sub/* end to end.
	handle /sub/* {
		reverse_proxy marzban:8000
	}

	# Everything else on this host. `abort` drops the connection without confirming that a panel is
	# behind it; a 404 page would advertise it.
	handle {
		abort
	}

	log
}
